{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/25039", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/25039/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/25039/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/25039/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/25039", "id": 72523739, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU3MjUyMzczOQ==", "number": 25039, "title": "FnMut sugar doesn't work through struct member variables", "user": {"login": "kaiskye", "id": 2130164, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIxMzAxNjQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2130164?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye", "html_url": "https://github.com/kaiskye", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2015-05-01T21:07:07Z", "updated_at": "2015-05-01T23:10:22Z", "closed_at": "2015-05-01T23:10:22Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "From what I understand, calling functions through an FnMut reference performs a sugaring operation that converts the call to call_mut(...). This doesn't seem to apply if the FnMut reference is stored inside of a struct.\n\nHere is an example that stores a reference to an FnMut trait inside of a struct.\n\n```\nstruct MyStruct<'a, F> where F: 'a + FnMut() {\n    func: &'a mut F\n}\n\nimpl<'a, F> MyStruct<'a, F> where F: 'a + FnMut() {\n    fn call_me(&mut self) {\n        // self.func() -- DOESN'T WORK\n        let mut f = &mut self.func;\n        f();\n    }\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let mut f = || {};\n    let mut s = MyStruct { func: &mut f };\n    s.call_me();\n}\n```\n\nCalling self.func() directly results in the following error:\n\n```\nerror: type `&mut MyStruct<'a, F>` does not implement any method in scope named `func`\n```\n\nHowever, binding self.func to a local variable and then calling through that compiles without errors.\n## Meta\n\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\n\n```\nrustc 1.0.0-beta.3 (5241bf9c3 2015-04-25) (built 2015-04-25)\nbinary: rustc\ncommit-hash: 5241bf9c34d156ea6064367a33cbd7222eeb5789\ncommit-date: 2015-04-25\nbuild-date: 2015-04-25\nhost: x86_64-pc-windows-gnu\nrelease: 1.0.0-beta.3\n```\n", "closed_by": {"login": "kaiskye", "id": 2130164, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIxMzAxNjQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2130164?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye", "html_url": "https://github.com/kaiskye", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kaiskye/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": fa